# Clojure Backend

## Request flow

`routes/*` → `handlers/*` → `db/*` → MongoDB

Routes stay thin; HTTP and validation in handlers; persistence in `db/`.

## Handlers

- Use `galaticos.util.response` — `resp/error`, `resp/server-error`, `resp/->object-id`
- Log errors with `clojure.tools.logging`
- Validate bodies with explicit allowed-field sets:

```clojure
(def ^:private allowed-player-fields #{:name :position ...})
(defn- validate-player-body [body]
  (let [unknown (seq (remove allowed-player-fields (keys body)))]
    (when unknown {:error (str "Unknown fields: " ...)})))
```

See `src/galaticos/handlers/players.clj` for the pattern.

## Routes

- Per-resource ns under `galaticos.routes.*`
- Mounted in `src/galaticos/routes/api.clj`

## Where logic lives

- Shared domain: `galaticos.championship.roster`, `galaticos.db.*`
- Analytics recompute: `galaticos.analytics.player-stats-jobs`
- Do not duplicate business rules in routes

## Exceptions

Map `ex-data :status` 400 to client errors; other exceptions → log + `server-error`.
